    "Certain fractions of random cells are repeatedly selected to test whether the local label distributions are statistically similar to the global label distributions (null hypothesis).",
    "The kBET value is the rejection rate over all tested neighborhoods, and values close to 0 indicate that the batches are well mixed.",
    "scIB adjusts the kBET with a diffusion-based correction to enable unbiased comparison on graph-and non-graph-based integration results.",
    "kBET values are first computed for each label and then averaged and subtracted from 1 to get a final kBET score.",
    "Modality alignment metrics."
